narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: Historical knowledge of hip-hop culture in America! Sedgwick and Cedar, Bronx Block Parties, sampling as an instrument, the rise of gangsta rap
I learned about the history of hip-hop and its culture, including its pioneers, sampling, breakbeats, and more in a fun and relaxed environment.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: Professor Conway is one of the most genuine and caring professors I've had at Yale. He's extremely knowledgeable about the subject matter.
This class was super fun and we learned a lot! The class was not stressful, but I feel like I still learned a lot from it.
The atmosphere was absolutely incredible, it was a joy coming to class every week and the little community that our class had was always good vibes.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: I would definitely recommend the course for anyone interested in hip-hop!
I 100% recommend it, Nick is so caring and knowledgable. Music video battles were a highlight of my semester.
Yes, absolutely try and take this class if you can. Professor Nick makes the experience wonderful.
